        public boolean containsUndeclaredUnits()
        Description copied from interface: SBaseWithDerivedUnit
        Returns true or false depending on whether this SBaseWithDerivedUnit refers to elements such as parameters or numbers with undeclared units. A return value of true indicates that the UnitDefinition returned by SBaseWithDerivedUnit.getDerivedUnitDefinition() may not accurately represent the units of the expression.

      • getDerivedUnitDefinition

        public UnitDefinition getDerivedUnitDefinition()
        Description copied from interface: SBaseWithDerivedUnit
        Derives the unit of this quantity and tries to identify an equivalent UnitDefinition within the corresponding Model. If no equivalent unit definition can be found, a new unit definition will be created that is not part of the model but represents the unit of this quantity. If it is not possible to derive a unit for this quantity, null will be returned.
        Specified by:
        getDerivedUnitDefinition in interface SBaseWithDerivedUnit
        Overrides:
        getDerivedUnitDefinition in class AbstractNamedSBaseWithUnit
        Returns:
        a UnitDefinition that represent the derived unit of this quantity, or null if it is not possible to derive a unit.

        @Deprecated
public String getSpatialSizeUnits()
        Deprecated. Only valid for SBML Level 2 Versions 1 and 2.
        If determined, this method first checks the explicitly set spatial size units of this Species. If no such value is defined, it will return the units of the surrounding Compartment. Only if this is also not possible, an empty String will be returned.
        Returns:
        the spatialSizeUnits of this Species.

      • getSpatialSizeUnitsInstance

        @Deprecated
public UnitDefinition getSpatialSizeUnitsInstance()
        Deprecated. Only valid for SBML Level 2 Versions 1 and 2.
        Determines the spatial units of this Species. If the spatial units have been set explicitly using spatialSizeUnitsID the corresponding UnitDefinition from the Model to which this Species belongs will be returned. Otherwise, the size unit from the surrounding Compartment of this Species will be returned. If this also fails, null will be returned.
        Returns:
        The UnitDefinition instance which as the spatialSizeUnitsID of this Species as id or the size unit of the surrounding Compartment. null if it doesn't exist.

      • writeXMLAttributes

        public Map<String,String> writeXMLAttributes()
        Description copied from interface: SBase
        Returns a map with all the attributes of this SBase that need to be written out in XML.

        The attribute name is used as a key and the attribute value as value. If a prefix is needed for the attribute name, it need to be set directly in this map.
